gomodel:SYNGO_1817  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors purify synaptic fractions (synaptosomes) from rat brain. They then isolate clathrin-coated vesicles (CCVs) from the synaptic fractions. They demonstrate that the vast majority of CCVs purified in this way are from the presysnapse and contain synaptic vesicles as their major cargo. Western blot reveals the enrichment of clathrin light chain B in these fractions (bottom band in figure 5).. Experimental description: In the abstract, \"...purified nerve terminals obtained from rat brain...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1817" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

